criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  first-ever unilateral stroke;

          -  hemiplegia resulting from stroke;

          -  age between 40 and 65 years old;

          -  presence of hypertonicity in the upper extremity;

          -  restricted range of motion of the shoulder

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  recurrent stroke;

          -  previous treatment with nerve blocks, motor point injections with neurolytic agents
             for spasticity at any time;

          -  previous treatment with BTX-A in the 6 months prior the study;

          -  severe cognitive deficits; 5, progressive or severe neurologic diseases, e.g., heart
             conditions, unstable hypertension, fracture or implants in the lower extremity;

          -  fear to needles;

          -  any contraindication for deep dry needling, e.g., anticoagulants, infections,
             bleeding, or psychotic.
